task.summary: I'm currently trying to convert into a JFX project but it's a pain in the ass I might just go back to swing.
changed the maven config file in hopes that it compiles.
So it sorta works now but fxml file won't open. I may be restrained to only use code to build gui.
The fxml import now works. I am playing around with the structure of javaFX to understand how it works.
I've gone back to coding the ui instead of trying to use fxml. i'll have a mainTab class from which all the other classes inherit ... I still don't know how i'm going to implement the controllers.

Got four tab working and talking to the server which is fucking awesome. I still need to get the Name of drones sorted out because at the moment their names are just their speed. I then need to figure out a way to get the prompt text to display after I add a supplier. I also need to start to think about the update functions and all which seems pretty easy ngl.

Only the Dish tab is left to design ... i have tried to create new classes for the Tabpane inside of the Dish Tab but I get an exception in application start method which means that I may have to create those tabs inside of the DishTab class.
I am going to rewrite the recipe tab as it doesn't need all that info. I am also going to implement a listener on the dish table so that the recipe table updates every time I select a specific dish.
I am now able to add and remove specific ingredients from dishes and it pretty intuitive to do so with the ui. I now need to manage to validations and such before adding the extensions.
